name: 1,1,1,2,2-pentafluoroethane
Reason: 1,1,1,2,2-pentafluoroethane is a perfluorinated compound, meaning all hydrogen atoms in the ethane molecule have been replaced by fluorine atoms. Fluorine is the most electronegative element, which leads to strong intermolecular dipole-dipole interactions. Each fluorine atom is estimated to increase the melting point by approximately 15°C. In this case, there are five fluorine atoms, so the total increase would be (15°C x 5) = 75°C.
